Hi Don,

i ran into the same error.

A post on stackoverflow was inspiring:

http://stackoverflow.com/questions/7678485/oracle-ora-01805-on-oracle-11g-database

So I  upgraded the timezone-version, and now i, too, can read these
pretty dates when using "ROracle"...

In short, what i did, to the good old database [as SYS-user]:


select version from v$timezone_file;
/*
   VERSION
----------
        11
*/
--- so, i upgraded to (the latest) TZ-version 14:
--- You have to be in Migrate-mode to run  dbms_dst.begin_upgrade, so first

shutdown immediate
---- and then
startup migrate;

begin
 dbms_dst.begin_upgrade(new_version => 14);
end;
/
---- restart the database (back to normal)
--  and run dbms_dst.upgrade_database:
shutdown immediate
---- and then
startup;

declare
  num_err number;
begin
   dbms_dst.upgrade_database(num_err);
   dbms_output.put_line('upgraded running into '||num_err||' errors');
   dbms_dst.end_upgrade(num_err);
   dbms_output.put_line('running into '||num_err||' errors to end upgrade');
end;
/

select version from v$timezone_file;

/*
   VERSION
----------
        14
*/

---- you also might have to re-install/re-link the "ROracle"-package
(as i did that without testing before-hand, i just cannot tell for
sure :)

hth;

best regards,
norbert hoeller
